In a speech at the Mayflower Hotel in Washington, D.C., President Joe Biden thanked organizations such as EMILY's List, NARAL, and Planned Parenthood for their endorsement and support. He emphasized the importance of protecting women's reproductive rights and criticized the recent Supreme Court decision in the Dobbs case. Biden vowed to fight for the restoration of Roe v. Wade and stated that he would veto any national ban on abortion. He also highlighted the need for women to be included in decision-making processes and discussed other issues such as paid leave and affordable childcare. The President called on the audience to continue their advocacy and expressed optimism about the future of the country.